info.name: Spinal cord, intermediate gray matter
info.description: The intermediate gray matter is that region of spinal cord gray matter between the dorsal (posterior) and ventral (anterior) horns.  It has characteristics of both dorsal and ventral horns and contains the preganglionic autonomic neurons as well as the Clark's nucleus (nucleus dorsalis).
